/**
 * Law Recordings Central API
 * 
 * Purpose: Single source of truth for recordings, users, and access control
 * 
 * Architecture:
 * - SQLite database (easy to migrate to PostgreSQL later)
 * - No auth yet (uses mock userId, ready for Supabase integration)
 * - REST API for both law app and future community app
 * - Receives webhooks from zoombot when recordings are ready
 * 
 * Pros:
 * - Centralized permission logic
 * - Multiple frontends can connect (law app, community app, mobile)
 * - Easy to add features (analytics, social, purchases)
 * - Database handles concurrency/consistency
 * 
 * Cons:
 * - Adds network latency (law app → API → database)
 * - Need to run API server (but simple with Railway/Heroku)
 * - More complex than direct file access
 * 
 * Alternative: Direct file system (current webhook-server.mjs approach)
 * - Pros: Simpler, no API needed, works offline
 * - Cons: Can't scale to multiple users, no permission system, hard to add community features
 */

